article.headline: Hartford 68, Albany, N.Y. 63
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Joe Zeglinski scored 19 points and grabbed 6 rebounds to lead Hartford over Albany, N.Y., 68-63 in America East Conference basketball Saturday. Zeglinski, who made 5-of-7 from 3-point range, hit a long-range jumper from right of the key to snap a 56-56 tie with 5:07 left to play, giving the Hawks a lead they would not relinquish. Michael Turner added 13 points for Hartford (13-13, 7-4), while Morgan Sabia scored 10. Hartford shot 50 percent from the floor, 76.2 percent from the foul line and made 8-of-18 from the 3-point range. Brian Lillis led Albany (11-12, 6-5) with 17 points. Brian Connelly added 10 and grabbed 6 rebounds. Brent Wilson also scored 10 points for Albany. Albany was 47.3 percent from the floor, 42.9 percent from the foul line and was 3-of-19 from beyond the arc.
